<ol><li>The<b> real image</b>&nbsp;of the distant object is formed in the focal plane of the objective.</li><li>The eyepiece is adjusted so its focal plane&nbsp;<b>coincides with the focal plane of the objective</b>.</li><li>The light rays from each point of the real image&nbsp;<b>leaves the eyepiece parallel to each other</b>, so they appear to come from a virtual image at infinity.</li></ol>